# Linux Home Lab

Personal Linux practice lab using Oracle VirtualBox running Kali Linux for cybersecurity learning.

## Lab Environment
- **Virtualization:** Oracle VirtualBox
- **OS:** Kali Linux
- **Purpose:** Hands-on Linux practice for entry-level cybersecurity

## Commands Learned

### User & System Info
| `whoami` | Shows current logged in user |
| `id` | Shows user ID and group details |
| `groups` | Shows groups your user belongs to |

### Navigation
| `pwd` | Print current directory location |
| `ls` | List files and folders |
| `cd foldername` | Change into a directory |
| `cd ..` | Go back one level |

### File Operations
| `cat filename` | Read contents of a file |
| `touch filename` | Create a new empty file |
| `find --name *.txt` | Find files by name/extension |

### Searching
| `echo "text"` | Print/repeat text in terminal |
| `grep "value" filename` | Search inside a single file |
| `grep -R "value" /folder/` | Search recursively through all files |

### File Viewing & Comparison
- `cat` with flags (-n for line numbers)
- `head` — view start of file (-n for lines, -c for bytes)
- `tail` — view end of file (-n for lines, -c for bytes)  
- `diff` — compare two files or folders (-r for recursive)

## Goal
Building foundational Linux skills to pursue an Cloud security role.
